\pagestyle{fancy}
\fancyhf{}
\fancyhead[L]{OpenClaw Setup Guide}
\fancyhead[R]{Claude Code + GitHub}
\fancyfoot[C]{\thepage}

\titleformat{\section}{\large\bfseries\color{blue!60!black}}{}{0em}{}

\setlist[itemize]{leftmargin=1.5em}

\begin{document}

\begin{center}
    {\LARGE \textbf{Simple Setup Guide}}\\[0.2cm]
    {\Large \textbf{OpenClaw, Claude Code, SSH and GitHub}}\\[0.3cm]
    \textbf{Beginner-Friendly Version}
\end{center}

\vspace{0.4cm}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=blue!5,colframe=blue!60!black,title=What This Setup Does]
This setup connects four things together:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item Your server
    \item OpenClaw
    \item Claude Code
    \item Your GitHub project
\end{enumerate}
\end{tcolorbox}

\section*{Step 1: Connect to Your Server}

Your server is the remote computer where OpenClaw runs.

Open Terminal or PowerShell and type:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{ssh YOUR\_USERNAME@YOUR\_SERVER\_IP}
\end{tcolorbox}

Example:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{ssh mike@192.168.1.20}
\end{tcolorbox}

If it asks:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=yellow!10,colframe=yellow!50!black]
\texttt{Are you sure you want to continue connecting?}
\end{tcolorbox}

Type:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{yes}
\end{tcolorbox}

Then enter your password.

\section*{Step 2: Check That OpenClaw Is Running}

Try this command:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{docker ps}
\end{tcolorbox}

If your setup does not use Docker, try:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{pm2 list}
\end{tcolorbox}

You should see OpenClaw listed as running.

\section*{Step 3: Check Claude Code}

Type:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{claude --version}
\end{tcolorbox}

If Claude Code is installed, it will show a version number.

If you see:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=red!5,colframe=red!60!black]
\texttt{command not found}
\end{tcolorbox}

then Claude Code is not installed yet.

\section*{Step 4: Connect GitHub}

Install GitHub CLI:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{sudo apt update}\\
\texttt{sudo apt install gh -y}
\end{tcolorbox}

Login to GitHub:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{gh auth login}
\end{tcolorbox}

Choose:

\begin{itemize}
    \item GitHub.com
    \item HTTPS
    \item Login with a web browser
\end{itemize}

GitHub will give you a code. Open:

\begin{center}
\url{https://github.com/login/device}
\end{center}

Enter the code shown in the terminal.

\section*{Step 5: Download Your Project}

Create a projects folder:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{mkdir projects}\\
\texttt{cd projects}
\end{tcolorbox}

Clone your project from GitHub:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{git clone https://github.com/YOURNAME/YOURPROJECT.git}
\end{tcolorbox}

Example:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{git clone https://github.com/mikereid/exam-grader.git}
\end{tcolorbox}

Go into the project:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{cd YOURPROJECT}
\end{tcolorbox}

\section*{Step 6: Start Claude Code}

Inside your project folder, type:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{claude}
\end{tcolorbox}

Then ask Claude:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=green!5,colframe=green!50!black]
Explain this project structure.
\end{tcolorbox}

\section*{Step 7: Use OpenClaw Chat}

In Telegram or OpenClaw chat, you can send simple instructions such as:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=green!5,colframe=green!50!black]
Open the project folder.
\end{tcolorbox}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=green!5,colframe=green!50!black]
Ask Claude to explain the frontend.
\end{tcolorbox}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=green!5,colframe=green!50!black]
Find bugs in the upload system.
\end{tcolorbox}

\section*{Simple Overview}

\begin{center}
\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=blue!5,colframe=blue!60!black,width=0.8\textwidth]
\centering
Your PC\\
$\downarrow$ SSH\\
Server\\
$\downarrow$\\
OpenClaw\\
$\downarrow$\\
Claude Code\\
$\downarrow$\\
Your GitHub Project
\end{tcolorbox}
\end{center}

\section*{First Test Commands}

After logging in with SSH, run only these three commands first:

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=gray!5,colframe=gray!60!black]
\texttt{claude --version}\\
\texttt{gh auth status}\\
\texttt{docker ps}
\end{tcolorbox}

\section*{What To Record}

Write down the result of each command:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|p{4cm}|p{5cm}|p{5cm}|}
\hline
\textbf{Command} & \textbf{Worked?} & \textbf{Error Message} \\
\hline
\texttt{claude --version} & & \\
\hline
\texttt{gh auth status} & & \\
\hline
\texttt{docker ps} & & \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\end{document}

